      <description>Up to this point, all of our programs have been written within a single file. There is nothing wrong with this â€“ a C program is just a bunch of functions, and it&amp;rsquo;s fine to group those functions within a single file. However, as your programs get bigger, it&amp;rsquo;s nice to physically separate functions into different files. This makes it easier to find certain pieces of your program.
Separating functions also promotes reuse.</description>
