    <item>
      <title>Pointers to Functions</title>
      <link>https://ksu-cs-textbooks.github.io/cis308/7-chapter/index.html</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Aug 2018 10:53:05 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ksu-cs-textbooks.github.io/cis308/7-chapter/index.html</guid>
      <description>The	pointers we	have looked	at	so	far	have	all	been	pointers	to	various	types	of	data	objects, (such	as	int,	char,	double,	struct	person,	and	pointer-to-int),	but	it	is	also	possible	to	have pointers	to	functions.	Pointers	to	functions	are	useful	for	approximately	the	same	reasons	as pointers	to	data:	when	you	want	an	extra	level	of	indirection, or	when	you&amp;rsquo;d	like	the	same	piece	of code	to	call	different	functions	depending	on	circumstances.</description>
